// @run
// @log 1
// FORWARD REFERENCE, un-annotated callee (A17). `a` calls `b`, which is defined
// LATER and has no `: returnType` annotation. Return-type inference is now
// demand-driven: when `a`'s body needs `b`'s return type and finds it an
// unresolved `Infer` hole, `b`'s body is inferred on the spot (out of source
// order) and memoized, so `b()` resolves to `i32` and satisfies `a`'s declared
// `i32` return. (Previously the hole stayed empty until `b`'s body was reached in
// source order, so the call froze to `any` and errored.)
function a(): i32 { return b() }
function b() { return 1 }
print(a())
